==Post-''Idol''==
In May 2009 ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' magazine confirmed his solo album was expected to be released in November 2009. Lambert stated that he would love to work with [[Slash (musician)|Slash]], stating "When I was working with Slash I felt at home." He also stated that his solo album would be eclectic, having a variety of sounds.<ref> [http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/news/american-idol-runner-up-adam-lambert-thrilled-1003976209.story] "'American Idol' Runner-Up Adam Lambert 'Thrilled' About The Future", ''Billboard Magazine'', May 22, 2009.</ref> Rock group [[Queen (band)|Queen]], with whom Lambert performed on the season finale, were at one point said to be considering asking Lambert to be their new [[Lead vocalist|frontman]].<ref> [http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/news/queen-considering-idol-s-lambert-as-frontman-1003976214.story] "Queen Considering 'Idol's' Lambert As Frontman", ''Billboard Magazine'', May 23, 2009.</ref> Lambert was a guest on ''[[Larry King Live]]'' (guest-hosted by [[Ryan Seacrest]]) along with [[Kris Allen]], judge [[Paula Abdul]], and the rest of the top ten finalists. In that appearance he stated that he planned to create a multi-genre album, calling it a "[[pop rock|rock-pop]]-[[electronica|electronic]]-[[dance music|dance]] thing".<ref>[http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5ghUIXxEvFDqm_ZlsTiEOcRZ9x9TwD98E8M580 ]{{dead link|date=March 2010}}</ref>  Lambert stuck to those intentions; the album he subsequently released conformed highly to his description of the album he planned to make.<ref name="review">{{cite news|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/music_blog/2009/11/album-review-adam-lamberts-for-your-entertainment.html|title=Album review: Adam Lambert's 'For Your Entertainment'|published=November 19, 2009|accessdate=December 10, 2009 | work=The Los Angeles Times | date=2009-11-19}}</ref>

Adam Lambert worked with producers [[Greg Wells]], [[Ryan Tedder]], [[Max Martin]], [[Sam Sparro]], [[RedOne]],<ref name="rollingstone.com"/> [[Dr. Luke]], and [[Linda Perry]], among others, in the run-up to the release of his debut album, ''For Your Entertainment''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lhwgsTCqQYA|title=YouTube <U+2013> 2009-08-23 Adam Lambert Interview with John Soeder (Plain Dealer Pop Music Critic)|accessdate=December 10, 2009}}</ref> [[Aimee Mayo]] stated on Twitter that she wrote at least two songs for Lambert,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://twitter.com/aimeemayo|title=Aimee Mayo (AimeeMayo) on Twitter|accessdate=December 10, 2009}}</ref> one co-written with Ryan Tedder and Chris Lindsey and, another with [[Ferras]], the latter of which was not included for selection. [[Lady Gaga]] also reportedly wrote a song that they spent some time recording.<ref name="twitter.com"> {{cite web|url=http://twitter.com/adamlambert|title=Adam Lambert (AdamLambert) on Twitter|accessdate=December 10, 2009}}</ref> On October 28, 2009, Lambert announced via Twitter that his lead single from his debut album would be "[[For Your Entertainment (song)|For Your Entertainment]]", a song that was produced by [[Dr. Luke]].<ref> {{cite web|url=http://twitter.com/adamlambert/status/5241677403|title=Twitter / Adam Lambert: Debut Single...|accessdate=December 10, 2009}}</ref> 

Lambert was recruited to record the soundtrack "[[Time for Miracles]]" for the disaster movie ''[[2012 (film)|2012]]'' that was released on October 20, 2009 as a side project single. The song was lauded ahead of its release by Queen's guitarist, [[Brian May]], who described himself as being "completely blown away" upon hearing the track.<ref>{{cite web|author=Daniel Kreps |url=http://www.rollingstone.com/rockdaily/index.php/2009/08/20/lamberts-2012-song-is-truly-sensational-brian-may-says/ |title=Lambert<U+2019>s <U+201C>2012 <U+201D> Song Is <U+201C>Truly Sensational,<U+201D> Brian May Says : Rolling Stone : Rock and Roll Daily |publisher=Rolling Stone |date= |accessdate=2010-03-24}}</ref>  The track "Time for Miracles" also appears on ''For Your Entertainment''.<ref name="billboard">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/search/?Nty=1&Ntx=mode%2Bmatchallpartial&Ntk=Keyword&Ns=FULL_DATE%7C1&Ne=125&N=126&Ntt=Adam%20Lambert#/album/adam-lambert/for-your-entertainment/1299259|title=For Your Entertainment - Adam Lambert , Billboard.com|accessdate=December 14, 2009}}</ref>

On June 19, 2009, [[Hi Fi Recordings]] and Wilshire Records revealed that they would be releasing ''On With the Show'', a compilation of songs Lambert had recorded prior to ''American Idol'' while working as a [[session musician]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Up for DiscussionPost Comment |url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/news/adam-lambert-pre-idol-debut-album-due-this-1003986264.story |title=Adam Lambert Pre-'Idol' Debut Album Due This Summer |publisher=Billboard.com |date=2009-09-14 |accessdate=2010-03-24}}</ref> The album's first single is "Want."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://video.google.com/videosearch?source=ig&hl=en&rlz=1G1GGLQ_ENUS307&q=on%20with%20the%20show%20lambert&um=1&ie=UTF-8&sa=N&tab=wv#q=want+adam+lambert&hl=en&emb=1 |title=on with the show lambert <U+2013> Google Videos |publisher=Video.google.com |date= |accessdate=2010-03-24}}</ref> Lambert later issued a statement through [[19 Entertainment]] stating, "Back in 2005 when I was a struggling artist, I was hired as a studio singer to lend my vocals to tracks written by someone else. I was broke at the time and this was my chance to make a few bucks, so I jumped at the opportunity to record for my first time in a professional studio. The work I did back then in no way reflects the music I am currently in the studio working on."<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/news/adam-lambert-pre-idol-debut-album-due-this-1003986264.story Billboard article: "Adam Lambert Pre-'Idol' Debut Album Due This Summer"]</ref> On November 17, Lambert's album was released with a new name: "''Take One''." The album is available on iTunes.

Since ''Idol'' Lambert has so far won two awards: the Young Hollywood Award for Artist of the Year and the Teen Choice Award for Reality/Variety Star.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.teenchoiceawards.com/pdf/TC09WINNERSFINALDB.pdf |title=Official Winners: 2009 Teen Choice Awards |accessdate=August 16, 2009|format=PDF}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url= http://www.yhawards.com/2009/winners.html |title=Young Hollywood Awards <U+2013> Winners <U+2013> 2009 |accessdate=August 16, 2009}}</ref> Lambert participated in the [[American Idols LIVE! Tour 2009]] with his fellow Top 10 contestants; the tour visited 50 cities in the United States and Canada from July 5 to September 15, 2009.

In November, Lambert performed "[[For Your Entertainment (song)|For Your Entertainment]]" at the [[American Music Awards of 2009]]. The performance showed Lambert kissing a male keyboardist, grinding a dancer's head against his pelvis, and grabbing the crotch of another. Lambert told ''Rolling Stone'' magazine, "Female performers have been doing this for years<U+2014>pushing the envelope about sexuality<U+2014>and the minute a man does it, everybody freaks out. We're in 2009<U+2014>it's time to take risks, be a little more brave, time to open people's eyes and if it offends them, then maybe I'm not for them. My goal was not to piss people off, it was to promote freedom of expression and artistic freedom."<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1626851/20091123/lambert_adam_american_idol.jhtml |title=Adam Lambert Says AMA Kiss Was 'In The Moment'|last=Kaufman|first=Gil|date=23 November 2009|publisher=MTV News|accessdate=23 November 2009}}</ref> In response to his performance, the [[Parents Television Council]], a conservative [[decency]] campaigning group,<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1039700,00.html |title=The Decency Police|author=Poniewozik, James|work= [[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=2005-03-20|accessdate=2009-10-14}}</ref> urged viewers to complain to the FCC.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.broadcastingcable.com/article/390281-PTC_Upset_Over_Adam_Lambert_AMA_Performance.php |title=PTC Upset Over Adam Lambert AMA Performance| last=Eggerton|first=John|date=23 November 2009|work=Broadcasting & Cable|accessdate=23 November 2009}}</ref> The performance, at the end of the show, was broadcast "outside the FCC's usual 6am-10pm time frame prohibiting the broadcast of indecent material".<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.rockstarweekly.com/content/view/1202/149/|title=Adam Lambert Could Cost ABC Television Up To $500,000 |date=23 November 2009|work= Rockstar Weekly|accessdate=23 November 2009}}</ref> ABC received about 1,500 telephoned complaints and announced he would not perform on [[Good Morning America]] on November 25 as planned.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://new.music.yahoo.com/adam-lambert/news/abc-lamberts-performance-draws-1-500-complaints--61996642 |title=ABC: Lambert's performance draws 1,500 complaints|date=23 November 2009|work=Yahoo! Music|agency=Associated Press|accessdate=23 November 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://omg.yahoo.com/news/updated-abcs-good-morning-america-cancels-adam-lamberts-performance/31728?nc |title=UPDATED: ABC's 'Good Morning America' Cancels Adam Lambert's Performance|date=24 November 2009|work=Yahoo News| publisher=Yahoo.com |accessdate=25 November 2009}}</ref> CBS subsequently invited Lambert to perform instead on ''[[The Early Show]]'', on the same date in New York City.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2009/11/24/earlyshow/leisure/celebspot/main5762324.shtml |title=Adam Lambert To Perform On "Early Show"|date=24 November 2009|work=CBS News|publisher=Cbsnews.com|accessdate=24 November 2009}}</ref>

February 27th, 2010 Lambert performed his first official solo concert, held at [[Fantasy Springs Resort Casino]] in Indio, California.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kesq.com/Global/story.asp?S=12058801 |title=Adam Lambert Performs in Front of Packed Crowd in Indio <U+2013> KESQ.com Palm Springs, Coachella Valley <U+2013> Weather, News, Sports: |publisher=Kesq.com |date=2010-02-28 |accessdate=2010-03-24}}</ref>  He appeared on ''American Idol'' as a guest mentor in an episode airing April 13, 2010.<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.nationalledger.com/artman/publish/article_272631211.shtml
|title=Adam Lambert <U+2013> Idol Mentor for This Year's Contestants 
|work=National Ledger 
|date=Apr 7, 2010
|accessdate=Apr 7, 2010
}}</ref> Adam Lambert is currently touring throughout the United States this summer with [[Allison Iraheta]] and [[Orianthi]]. He will be touring until December and he is taking the Glam Nation tour internationally. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2010/04/american-idol-allison-iraheta-orianthi-join-adam-lambert-tour.html |title='American Idol': Allison Iraheta, Orianthi join Adam Lambert tour |publisher=zap2it.com |date=2010-04-27 |accessdate=2010-06-06}}</ref>

